  "original_title": "IUSF goes to HRCSL over arrests",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "IUSF goes to HRCSL over arrests",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "COLOMBO (News 1st); The Inter-University Student Union lodged a complaint at the Human Rights Commission of Sri Lanka (HRCSL) with regard to Tuesday's (30) incidents, including the arrest of 28 members.",
        "Venerable Pokunavita Piyasoma Thera, a representative of the IUSF asked how the Government continues to deploy the police to stop the protests, when the people of the country do not have enough food, cooking gas, and medicines.",
        "Venerable Pokunavita Piyasoma Thera pointed out that due to these factors, children's education has also come to a halt.",
        "\"We cannot wait at home when these things are happening. We have to take it to the streets. They attacked the protestors who took it to the streets. But the Rajapaksa regime chased these peaceful protestors around with batons in hand, and even attacked them with water cannon and tear gas,\" Ven. Piyasoma Thero said.",
        "28 members of the IUSF, who were arrested during a protest staged in Maradana on Tuesday (30), were released on bail on Wednesday (31).",
        "One-month-old infant abandoned at a motor garage with a letter",
        "Are you a victim of Cyber Crime? Police Unit ready to crackdown crime in the cyberspace"
      ],
